org.kiji.schema.impl.hbase
Class KijiHTablePool

java.lang.Object
  org.kiji.schema.impl.hbase.KijiHTablePool
All Implemented Interfaces:
Closeable
@ApiAudience.Private
public final class KijiHTablePool
extends Object
implements Closeable

This private class is designed to serve as a replacement for HTablePool, to get around the following HBase issues in the face of master failures:

  • https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6580
  • https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6956
  • https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4805
We accomplish this by creating a simple pool and a Pooled implementation of HTableInterface, similar to how HTablePool works. Unlike HTablePool, however, we verify the underlying connection before returning an instance from this pool. This implementation is also tied to a particular table name. You may construct a KijiHTablePool using the constructor KijiHTablePool(String, org.kiji.schema.impl.HTableInterfaceFactory ). Note that the provided HTableInterfaceFactory must return HTables rather than another implementation of HTableInterface. We rely on this to test connectivity. Once created, use {@link #getTable()} to generate HTableInterface instances. They will be returned to the pool automatically when closed. When you are finished with the pool, it should be closed to destroy any outstanding connections.
